cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on modelling the stochastic evolution of populations of agents.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper deals with spatial distribution and aggregation of populations, which can be seen as a network problem.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper presents a heuristic approach to reducing the computational cost of analysis, which can be seen as a control problem.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper combines stochastic approximation ideas with computational statistics to obtain an efficient aggregation, which involves algorithmic techniques.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses spectral clustering, which is a machine learning technique, to obtain the aggregation.
